<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="52">
<taxonomicName LSID="6ED11CB4-6D7E-52BB-A988-498636BE35DC" authority="Hook. f. (Fl. Brit. India 2: 318. 1878)." authorityName="Hook. f. (Fl. Brit. India 2: 318. 1878)." class="Mammalia" family="Astrapotheriidae" genus="Maddenia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Maddenia pedicellata" order="Astrapotheria" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pedicellata">Maddenia pedicellata Hook.f. (Fl. Brit. India 2: 318. 1878).</taxonomicName>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="52" type="type">
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="52">Type:</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="52">India. Mishmi Hills, Griffith s.n. (holotype: K!, K000396854).</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="13" pageNumber="52" type="note">
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="52">Note:</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="13" pageNumber="52">
As noted by 
<bibRefCitation author="Hooker, JD" editor="Hooker, JD" journalOrPublisher="2. L. Reeve &amp; Co., London" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" pagination="307 - 388" refId="B6" refString="Hooker, JD, 1878. Rosaceae. In: Hooker, JD, Ed., Flora of British India, vol. 2. L. Reeve &amp; Co., London: 307 - 388" title="Rosaceae." volumeTitle="Flora of British India, vol." year="1878">Hooker (1878)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName class="Mammalia" family="Astrapotheriidae" genus="Maddenia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Astrapotheria" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pedicellata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">Maddenia pedicellata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described based on a fragmentary specimen collected by Griffith from the Mishmi Hills. It was stated to be characterized by subcorymbose flowers on long slender pedicels on a short peduncle in unripe fruits (
<bibRefCitation author="Hooker, JD" editor="Hooker, JD" journalOrPublisher="2. L. Reeve &amp; Co., London" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" pagination="307 - 388" refId="B6" refString="Hooker, JD, 1878. Rosaceae. In: Hooker, JD, Ed., Flora of British India, vol. 2. L. Reeve &amp; Co., London: 307 - 388" title="Rosaceae." volumeTitle="Flora of British India, vol." year="1878">Hooker 1878</bibRefCitation>
, p. 318). The type was mounted on a sheet with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="J. Wen" authorityYear="2012" class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Rosaceae" genus="Prunus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Rosales" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="gongshanensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">Prunus gongshanensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
collected from Bhutan (Griffith 2057, K) in flower condition, although 
<bibRefCitation author="Hara, H" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Japanese Botany" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" pagination="7 - 11" refId="B4" refString="Hara, H, 1976. New or noteworthy flowering plants from Eastern Himalaya (17). Journal of Japanese Botany 51 (1): 7 - 11" title="New or noteworthy flowering plants from Eastern Himalaya (17)." volume="51" year="1976">Hara (1976)</bibRefCitation>
said it was a collection of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Hook fil &amp; Thomson" authorityYear="1854" class="Mammalia" family="Astrapotheriidae" genus="Maddenia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Astrapotheria" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="himalaica">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">Maddenia himalaica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which should bear highly pubescent leaves. This specimen has glabrous lower leaf surfaces with only traces of hairs at the axils of veins on the lower leaves. Our examination of the type material confirms 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Haraâ€™s">Hara's</normalizedToken>
treatment of 
<taxonomicName class="Mammalia" family="Astrapotheriidae" genus="Maddenia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Astrapotheria" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pedicellata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">Maddenia pedicellata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a synonym of 
<taxonomicName class="Dicotyledoneae" family="Rosaceae" genus="Prunus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Rosales" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" phylum="Angiospermae" rank="species" species="cerasoides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="13" pageNumber="52">Prunus cerasoides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Buchanan-Hamilton ex D. Don (
<bibRefCitation author="Hara, H" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Japanese Botany" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" pagination="7 - 11" refId="B4" refString="Hara, H, 1976. New or noteworthy flowering plants from Eastern Himalaya (17). Journal of Japanese Botany 51 (1): 7 - 11" title="New or noteworthy flowering plants from Eastern Himalaya (17)." volume="51" year="1976">Hara 1976</bibRefCitation>
; also see 
<bibRefCitation author="Lu, L" editor="Wu, ZY" journalOrPublisher="9. Science Press, Beijing; Missouri Botanical Garden Press, St. Louis" pageId="13" pageNumber="52" pagination="46 - 434" refId="B10" refString="Lu, L, Gu, C, Li, C, Alexander, C, Bartholomew, B, Brach, A, Boufford, DE, Ikeda, H, Ohba, H, Robertson, KR, Spongberg, SA, 2003. Rosaceae. In: Wu, ZY, Raven, PH, Eds., , Flora of China, vol. 9. Science Press, Beijing; Missouri Botanical Garden Press, St. Louis: 46 - 434" title="Rosaceae." volumeTitle=", Flora of China, vol." year="2003">Lu et al. 2003</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
